{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BQX2oRTAHKEGBbB4gcaiFS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.math.RoundingMode;\n    20→import java.util.Collection;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * MIGRATION NOTE: Updated to use RoundingMode enum instead of deprecated BigDecimal constants.\n    26→ */\n    27→public class FinancialUtils {\n    28→\n    29→    public static final RoundingMode ROUND = RoundingMode.HALF_UP;\n    30→    public static final int SCALE = 2;\n    31→    public static final BigDecimal ZERO = new BigDecimal(\"0.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    32→    public static final BigDecimal ONE = new BigDecimal(\"1.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    33→    public static final BigDecimal HUNDRED = new BigDecimal(\"100.00\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    34→\n    35→    public static BigDecimal computeGain(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    36→        return currentBalance.subtract(openBalance).setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public static BigDecimal computeGainPercent(BigDecimal currentBalance, BigDecimal openBalance) {\n    40→        if (openBalance.doubleValue() == 0.0) {\n    41→            return ZERO;\n    42→        }\n    43→        BigDecimal gainPercent = currentBalance.divide(openBalance, SCALE, ROUND)\n    44→                .subtract(ONE)\n    45→                .multiply(HUNDRED);\n    46→        return gainPercent;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static BigDecimal computeHoldingsTotal(Collection<?> holdingDataBeans) {\n    50→        BigDecimal holdingsTotal = new BigDecimal(\"0.0\").setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    51→        if (holdingDataBeans == null) {\n    52→            return holdingsTotal;\n    53→        }\n    54→        for (Object obj : holdingDataBeans) {\n    55→            HoldingDataBean holdingData = (HoldingDataBean) obj;\n    56→            BigDecimal total = holdingData.getPurchasePrice()\n    57→                    .multiply(new BigDecimal(holdingData.getQuantity()));\n    58→            holdingsTotal = holdingsTotal.add(total);\n    59→        }\n    60→        return holdingsTotal.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    public static String printGainHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    64→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    65→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    66→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    67→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    68→        } else {\n    69→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    70→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    71→        }\n    72→\n    73→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND) + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    74→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    75→        return htmlString;\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    public static String printChangeHTML(double change) {\n    79→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    80→        if (change < 0.0) {\n    81→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    82→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    83→        } else {\n    84→            htmlString = \"<FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">\";\n    85→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n    86→        }\n    87→\n    88→        htmlString += change + \"</FONT><IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n    89→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n    90→        return htmlString;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    public static String printGainPercentHTML(BigDecimal gain) {\n    94→        String htmlString, arrow;\n    95→        if (gain.doubleValue() < 0.0) {\n    96→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#ff0000\\\">\";\n    97→            arrow = \"arrowdown.gif\";\n    98→        } else {\n    99→            htmlString = \"(<B><FONT color=\\\"#009900\\\">+\";\n   100→            arrow = \"arrowup.gif\";\n   101→        }\n   102→\n   103→        htmlString += gain.setScale(SCALE, ROUND);\n   104→        htmlString += \"%</FONT></B>)<IMG src=\\\"images/\" + arrow \n   105→                + \"\\\" width=\\\"10\\\" height=\\\"10\\\" border=\\\"0\\\"></IMG>\";\n   106→        return htmlString;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public static String printQuoteLink(String symbol) {\n   110→        return \"<A href=\\\"app?action=quotes&symbols=\" + symbol + \"\\\">\" + symbol + \"</A>\";\n   111→    }\n   112→}\n   113→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"2f582f14-fe0a-46e9-884f-1f1a85e861f8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SggSFuRGor92veV1CW2WcK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.AbstractSequentialList;\n    19→import java.util.ListIterator;\n    20→\n    21→public class KeyBlock extends AbstractSequentialList<Object> {\n    22→\n    23→    // min and max provide range of valid primary keys for this KeyBlock\n    24→    private int min = 0;\n    25→    private int max = 0;\n    26→    private int index = 0;\n    27→\n    28→    /**\n    29→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    30→     */\n    31→    public KeyBlock() {\n    32→        super();\n    33→        min = 0;\n    34→        max = 0;\n    35→        index = min;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    40→     */\n    41→    public KeyBlock(int min, int max) {\n    42→        super();\n    43→        this.min = min;\n    44→        this.max = max;\n    45→        index = min;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    /**\n    49→     * @see AbstractCollection#size()\n    50→     */\n    51→    @Override\n    52→    public int size() {\n    53→        return (max - min) + 1;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * @see AbstractSequentialList#listIterator(int)\n    58→     */\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    public ListIterator<Object> listIterator(int arg0) {\n    61→        return new KeyBlockIterator();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    class KeyBlockIterator implements ListIterator<Object> {\n    65→\n    66→        /**\n    67→         * @see ListIterator#hasNext()\n    68→         */\n    69→        @Override\n    70→        public boolean hasNext() {\n    71→            return index <= max;\n    72→        }\n    73→\n    74→        /**\n    75→         * @see ListIterator#next()\n    76→         */\n    77→        @Override\n    78→        public synchronized Object next() {\n    79→            if (index > max) {\n    80→                throw new java.lang.RuntimeException(\"KeyBlock:next() -- Error KeyBlock depleted\");\n    81→            }\n    82→            return new Integer(index++);\n    83→        }\n    84→\n    85→        /**\n    86→         * @see ListIterator#hasPrevious()\n    87→         */\n    88→        @Override\n    89→        public boolean hasPrevious() {\n    90→            return index > min;\n    91→        }\n    92→\n    93→        /**\n    94→         * @see ListIterator#previous()\n    95→         */\n    96→        @Override\n    97→        public Object previous() {\n    98→            return new Integer(--index);\n    99→        }\n   100→\n   101→        /**\n   102→         * @see ListIterator#nextIndex()\n   103→         */\n   104→        @Override\n   105→        public int nextIndex() {\n   106→            return index - min;\n   107→        }\n   108→\n   109→        /**\n   110→         * @see ListIterator#previousIndex()\n   111→         */\n   112→        @Override\n   113→        public int previousIndex() {\n   114→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: previousIndex() not supported\");\n   115→        }\n   116→\n   117→        /**\n   118→         * @see ListIterator#add()\n   119→         */\n   120→        @Override\n   121→        public void add(Object o) {\n   122→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: add() not supported\");\n   123→        }\n   124→\n   125→        /**\n   126→         * @see ListIterator#remove()\n   127→         */\n   128→        @Override\n   129→        public void remove() {\n   130→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: remove() not supported\");\n   131→        }\n   132→\n   133→        /**\n   134→         * @see ListIterator#set(Object)\n   135→         */\n   136→        @Override\n   137→        public void set(Object arg0) {\n   138→        }\n   139→    }\n   140→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"453c3424-7878-4f3f-95dd-cfba75fb44f4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WMsZKQmUALpL5R4L185PAa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2022.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collection;\n    19→import java.util.Iterator;\n    20→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    21→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    22→\n    23→/**\n    24→ * MIGRATION NOTE: This class remains largely unchanged.\n    25→ * In Quarkus, you could also use JBoss Logging or SLF4J.\n    26→ * Quarkus uses JBoss LogManager by default.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class Log {\n    29→\n    30→    private final static Logger log = Logger.getLogger(\"daytrader\");\n    31→\n    32→    public static void log(String message) {\n    33→        log.log(Level.INFO, message);\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2) {\n    37→        log(msg1 + msg2);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n    41→        log(msg1 + msg2 + msg3);\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public static void error(String message) {\n    45→        message = \"Error: \" + message;\n    46→        log.severe(message);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public static void error(String message, Throwable e) {\n    50→        error(message + \"\\n\\t\" + e.toString());\n    51→        e.printStackTrace(System.out);\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public static void error(String msg1, String msg2, Throwable e) {\n    55→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public static void error(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3, Throwable e) {\n    59→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\" + msg3 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public static void error(Throwable e, String message) {\n    63→        error(message + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    64→        e.printStackTrace(System.out);\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    public static void error(Throwable e, String msg1, String msg2) {\n    68→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    69→    }\n    70→\n    71→    public static void error(Throwable e, String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n    72→        error(msg1 + \"\\n\" + msg2 + \"\\n\" + msg3 + \"\\n\\t\", e);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    public static void trace(String message) {\n    76→        log.log(Level.FINE, message + \" threadID=\" + Thread.currentThread());\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    public static void traceInterceptor(String message, Object parm1) {\n    80→        log.log(Level.SEVERE, message, parm1);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1) {\n    84→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \")\");\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2) {\n    88→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \")\");\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3) {\n    92→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \")\");\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4) {\n    96→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \")\");\n    97→    }\n    98→\n    99→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5) {\n   100→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \")\");\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5, Object parm6) {\n   104→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \", \" + parm6 + \")\");\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    public static void trace(String message, Object parm1, Object parm2, Object parm3, Object parm4, Object parm5, Object parm6, Object parm7) {\n   108→        trace(message + \"(\" + parm1 + \", \" + parm2 + \", \" + parm3 + \", \" + parm4 + \", \" + parm5 + \", \" + parm6 + \", \" + parm7 + \")\");\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    public static void traceEnter(String message) {\n   112→        log.entering(\"Log\", message);\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public static void traceExit(String message) {\n   116→        log.exiting(\"Log\", message);\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public static void stat(String message) {\n   120→        log(message);\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    public static void debug(String message) {\n   124→        log.log(Level.FINE, message);\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public static void print(String message) {\n   128→        log(message);\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    public static void printObject(Object o) {\n   132→        log(\"\\t\" + o.toString());\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    @SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\")\n   136→    public static void printCollection(Collection c) {\n   137→        log(\"\\t---Collection---\");\n   138→        if (c == null) {\n   139→            return;\n   140→        }\n   141→        Iterator it = c.iterator();\n   142→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   143→            log(\"\\t\\t\" + it.next().toString());\n   144→        }\n   145→        log(\"\\t---Collection---\");\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public static void printCollection(String message, Collection<?> c) {\n   149→        log(message);\n   150→        printCollection(c);\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    public static boolean doActionTrace() {\n   154→        return getTrace() && getActionTrace();\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    public static boolean doTrace() {\n   158→        return getTrace();\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    public static boolean doDebug() {\n   162→        return true;\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public static boolean doStat() {\n   166→        return true;\n   167→    }\n   168→\n   169→    public static boolean getTrace() {\n   170→        return TradeConfig.getTrace();\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    public static boolean getActionTrace() {\n   174→        return TradeConfig.getActionTrace();\n   175→    }\n   176→}\n   177→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"80c526b2-902a-4269-bca1-89fd50fb4733"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018hTMVkugXkGTLcDiTdHWAg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class MDBStats extends java.util.HashMap<String, TimerStat> {\n    25→\n    26→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -3759835921094193760L;\n    27→    // Singleton class\n    28→    private static MDBStats mdbStats = null;\n    29→\n    30→    private MDBStats() {\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    public static synchronized MDBStats getInstance() {\n    34→        if (mdbStats == null) {\n    35→            mdbStats = new MDBStats();\n    36→        }\n    37→        return mdbStats;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public TimerStat addTiming(String type, long sendTime, long recvTime) {\n    41→        TimerStat stats = null;\n    42→        synchronized (type) {\n    43→\n    44→            stats = get(type);\n    45→            if (stats == null) {\n    46→                stats = new TimerStat();\n    47→            }\n    48→\n    49→            long time = recvTime - sendTime;\n    50→            if (time > stats.getMax()) {\n    51→                stats.setMax(time);\n    52→            }\n    53→            if (time < stats.getMin()) {\n    54→                stats.setMin(time);\n    55→            }\n    56→            stats.setCount(stats.getCount() + 1);\n    57→            stats.setTotalTime(stats.getTotalTime() + time);\n    58→\n    59→            put(type, stats);\n    60→        }\n    61→        return stats;\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public synchronized void reset() {\n    65→        clear();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"e5d57278-2e73-4ca5-a950-f907fef9e8d2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D2XUW9oVnr8xt8ArPYQcRo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    24→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    25→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.QuotePriceChange;\n    29→\n    30→\n    31→/** This class is a holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary WebSocket\n    32→ *  and the JAX-RS SSE Broadcaster\n    33→ *  It fires a CDI event everytime a price change is added\n    34→ **/\n    35→\n    36→@ApplicationScoped\n    37→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList  {\n    38→\n    39→  private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    40→  private int maxSize = 5;\n    41→\n    42→  @Inject\n    43→  @QuotePriceChange\n    44→  Event<String> quotePriceChangeEvent;\n    45→\n    46→  public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    47→\n    48→    int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    49→\n    50→    if ( symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    51→      list.add(0, quoteData);\n    52→\n    53→      // Add stock, remove if needed\n    54→      if(list.size() > maxSize) {\n    55→        list.remove(maxSize);\n    56→      }      \n    57→      // Fire async event without ManagedExecutorService (Quarkus handles async events differently)\n    58→      quotePriceChangeEvent.fireAsync(\"quotePriceChange for symbol: \" + quoteData.getSymbol());\n    59→    }\n    60→    return true;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n    64→    return list.isEmpty();\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Size(max=5)\n    68→  @NotEmpty\n    69→  public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    70→    return list;\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"8f41062b-9f21-47d3-a01c-328d432d62d2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TZt2RgGNebzF4pUzDU3hcr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class TimerStat {\n    25→\n    26→    private double min = 1000000000.0, max = 0.0, totalTime = 0.0;\n    27→    private int count;\n    28→\n    29→    /**\n    30→     * Returns the count.\n    31→     *\n    32→     * @return int\n    33→     */\n    34→    public int getCount() {\n    35→        return count;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Returns the max.\n    40→     *\n    41→     * @return double\n    42→     */\n    43→    public double getMax() {\n    44→        return max;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    /**\n    48→     * Returns the min.\n    49→     *\n    50→     * @return double\n    51→     */\n    52→    public double getMin() {\n    53→        return min;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * Sets the count.\n    58→     *\n    59→     * @param count\n    60→     *            The count to set\n    61→     */\n    62→    public void setCount(int count) {\n    63→        this.count = count;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Sets the max.\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @param max\n    70→     *            The max to set\n    71→     */\n    72→    public void setMax(double max) {\n    73→        this.max = max;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    /**\n    77→     * Sets the min.\n    78→     *\n    79→     * @param min\n    80→     *            The min to set\n    81→     */\n    82→    public void setMin(double min) {\n    83→        this.min = min;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    /**\n    87→     * Returns the totalTime.\n    88→     *\n    89→     * @return double\n    90→     */\n    91→    public double getTotalTime() {\n    92→        return totalTime;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    /**\n    96→     * Sets the totalTime.\n    97→     *\n    98→     * @param totalTime\n    99→     *            The totalTime to set\n   100→     */\n   101→    public void setTotalTime(double totalTime) {\n   102→        this.totalTime = totalTime;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Returns the max in Secs\n   107→     *\n   108→     * @return double\n   109→     */\n   110→    public double getMaxSecs() {\n   111→        return max / 1000.0;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    /**\n   115→     * Returns the min in Secs\n   116→     *\n   117→     * @return double\n   118→     */\n   119→    public double getMinSecs() {\n   120→        return min / 1000.0;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * Returns the average time in Secs\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @return double\n   127→     */\n   128→    public double getAvgSecs() {\n   129→\n   130→        double avg = getTotalTime() / getCount();\n   131→        return avg / 1000.0;\n   132→    }\n   133→}\n   134→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"cbd6d484-331e-4ca2-974a-4dbc0093e6cd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLCrcPzTdQPcutMup7JNXD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→\n     6→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.given;\n     7→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.is;\n     8→\n     9→@QuarkusTest\n    10→class TradeResourceTest {\n    11→\n    12→    @Test\n    13→    void testMarketSummaryEndpoint() {\n    14→        given()\n    15→            .when().get(\"/rest/trade/market\")\n    16→            .then()\n    17→            .statusCode(200);\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"95a24c1c-3b3d-4667-bf80-8ac35bb770a0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CMZGhV9thi22HDy7x1rSyV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n    17→\n    18→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n    19→import io.restassured.http.ContentType;\n    20→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n    21→\n    22→import static io.restassured.RestAssured.given;\n    23→import static org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.*;\n    24→\n    25→/**\n    26→ * Tests for the messaging functionality.\n    27→ * These tests verify that the JMS-to-Reactive-Messaging migration works correctly.\n    28→ * \n    29→ * MIGRATION NOTES:\n    30→ * These tests replace manual testing of:\n    31→ * - PingServlet2MDBQueue -> /rest/messaging/ping/broker\n    32→ * - PingServlet2MDBTopic -> /rest/messaging/ping/streamer\n    33→ */\n    34→@QuarkusTest\n    35→public class MessagingResourceTest {\n    36→\n    37→    @Test\n    38→    public void testPingBroker() {\n    39→        given()\n    40→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    41→            .queryParam(\"message\", \"Test ping to broker\")\n    42→        .when()\n    43→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/broker\")\n    44→        .then()\n    45→            .statusCode(200)\n    46→            .body(\"status\", is(\"sent\"))\n    47→            .body(\"destination\", is(\"trade-broker-queue\"))\n    48→            .body(\"message\", is(\"Test ping to broker\"));\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    @Test\n    52→    public void testPingBrokerWithDefaultMessage() {\n    53→        given()\n    54→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    55→        .when()\n    56→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/broker\")\n    57→        .then()\n    58→            .statusCode(200)\n    59→            .body(\"status\", is(\"sent\"))\n    60→            .body(\"destination\", is(\"trade-broker-queue\"))\n    61→            .body(\"message\", containsString(\"Ping from MessagingResource\"));\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    @Test\n    65→    public void testPingStreamer() {\n    66→        given()\n    67→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    68→            .queryParam(\"message\", \"Test ping to streamer\")\n    69→        .when()\n    70→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/streamer\")\n    71→        .then()\n    72→            .statusCode(200)\n    73→            .body(\"status\", is(\"sent\"))\n    74→            .body(\"destination\", is(\"trade-streamer-topic\"))\n    75→            .body(\"message\", is(\"Test ping to streamer\"));\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    @Test\n    79→    public void testGetStats() {\n    80→        // First send some messages to generate stats\n    81→        given()\n    82→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    83→        .when()\n    84→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/broker\");\n    85→\n    86→        given()\n    87→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n    88→        .when()\n    89→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/ping/streamer\");\n    90→\n    91→        // Wait a bit for async processing\n    92→        try {\n    93→            Thread.sleep(500);\n    94→        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    95→            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\n    96→        }\n    97→\n    98→        // Then check stats\n    99→        given()\n   100→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n   101→        .when()\n   102→            .get(\"/rest/messaging/stats\")\n   103→        .then()\n   104→            .statusCode(200)\n   105→            .body(\"statistics\", notNullValue())\n   106→            .body(\"timestamp\", notNullValue());\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @Test\n   110→    public void testResetStats() {\n   111→        given()\n   112→            .contentType(ContentType.JSON)\n   113→        .when()\n   114→            .post(\"/rest/messaging/stats/reset\")\n   115→        .then()\n   116→            .statusCode(200)\n   117→            .body(\"status\", is(\"reset\"));\n   118→    }\n   119→}\n   120→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"3eb09266-ec22-4b35-9021-3b68edbdc30c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SHX4GQGuzRbTfueKj6kxXB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest;\n     4→import io.restassured.RestAssured;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→\n     7→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     8→\n     9→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    10→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    11→\n    12→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Tests for JMS to Reactive Messaging migration.\n    16→ * \n    17→ * These tests verify that:\n    18→ * 1. Messages can be sent via MessageProducerService\n    19→ * 2. Messages are received by DTBroker3MDB and DTStreamer3MDB\n    20→ * 3. MDBStats tracks message processing statistics\n    21→ */\n    22→@QuarkusTest\n    23→public class MessagingTest {\n    24→\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    MessageProducerService messageProducer;\n    27→\n    28→    @Test\n    29→    public void testBrokerPing() throws Exception {\n    30→        // Reset stats\n    31→        MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n    32→        \n    33→        // Send ping message\n    34→        messageProducer.sendBrokerPing(\"Test ping from MessagingTest\");\n    35→        \n    36→        // Give time for async processing\n    37→        Thread.sleep(500);\n    38→        \n    39→        // Verify stats were recorded (using original MDB class name)\n    40→        TimerStat stats = MDBStats.getInstance().get(\"DTBroker3MDB:ping\");\n    41→        assertNotNull(stats, \"Ping stats should be recorded\");\n    42→        assertTrue(stats.getCount() >= 1, \"At least one ping should be processed\");\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    @Test\n    46→    public void testStreamerPing() throws Exception {\n    47→        // Reset stats\n    48→        MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n    49→        \n    50→        // Send ping message to streamer\n    51→        messageProducer.sendStreamerPing(\"Test ping to streamer\");\n    52→        \n    53→        // Give time for async processing\n    54→        Thread.sleep(500);\n    55→        \n    56→        // Verify stats were recorded (using original MDB class name)\n    57→        TimerStat stats = MDBStats.getInstance().get(\"DTStreamer3MDB:ping\");\n    58→        assertNotNull(stats, \"Streamer ping stats should be recorded\");\n    59→        assertTrue(stats.getCount() >= 1, \"At least one streamer ping should be processed\");\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    @Test\n    63→    public void testQuoteUpdate() throws Exception {\n    64→        // Reset stats\n    65→        MDBStats.getInstance().reset();\n    66→        \n    67→        // Publish quote update\n    68→        messageProducer.publishQuoteUpdate(\"s:0\", \n    69→            new java.math.BigDecimal(\"105.50\"), \n    70→            new java.math.BigDecimal(\"100.00\"));\n    71→        \n    72→        // Give time for async processing\n    73→        Thread.sleep(500);\n    74→        \n    75→        // Verify stats were recorded (using original MDB class name)\n    76→        TimerStat stats = MDBStats.getInstance().get(\"DTStreamer3MDB:updateQuote\");\n    77→        assertNotNull(stats, \"Quote update stats should be recorded\");\n    78→        assertTrue(stats.getCount() >= 1, \"At least one quote update should be processed\");\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    @Test\n    82→    public void testAsyncOrderProcessing() throws Exception {\n    83→        // First create an order via REST API\n    84→        // The TradeAppResource uses POST to /rest/app with action parameter\n    85→        String loginResponse = RestAssured.given()\n    86→            .formParam(\"action\", \"login\")\n    87→            .formParam(\"uid\", \"uid:0\")\n    88→            .formParam(\"passwd\", \"xxx\")\n    89→            .when()\n    90→            .post(\"/rest/app\")\n    91→            .then()\n    92→            .statusCode(200)\n    93→            .extract().body().asString();\n    94→\n    95→        // Buy a stock (this creates an order)\n    96→        String buyResponse = RestAssured.given()\n    97→            .formParam(\"action\", \"buy\")\n    98→            .formParam(\"symbol\", \"s:0\")\n    99→            .formParam(\"quantity\", \"10\")\n   100→            .when()\n   101→            .post(\"/rest/app\")\n   102→            .then()\n   103→            .statusCode(200)\n   104→            .extract().body().asString();\n   105→\n   106→        assertTrue(buyResponse.contains(\"Order\") || buyResponse.contains(\"order\"), \n   107→            \"Buy should create an order\");\n   108→    }\n   109→}\n   110→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"6195a014-a0ee-4fdb-8a82-df97f437a1bd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016naNG9zCBZSSMCCKfBocss","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have successfully read all 23 files. Here are the complete contents of each file:\n\n---\n\n## 1. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java\n\nThis is a JPA entity representing a trading account with 267 lines. Key features:\n- Uses Jakarta Persistence (migrated from javax)\n- IDENTITY generation strategy for primary key\n- Relationships: OneToMany with orders and holdings, OneToOne with profile\n- Business methods: login(), logout()\n- Includes validation annotations (@NotNull, @PositiveOrZero, @PastOrPresent)\n\n---\n\n## 2. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountProfileDataBean.java\n\nAccount profile entity with 190 lines containing user information:\n- UserID as primary key\n- Fields: password, fullName, address, email, creditCard\n- Email validation using @Email annotation\n- OneToOne relationship with AccountDataBean\n- Factory method getRandomInstance() for test data generation\n\n---\n\n## 3. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/HoldingDataBean.java\n\nHolding entity representing stock ownership with 211 lines:\n- IDENTITY primary key generation\n- Fields: quantity, purchasePrice, purchaseDate\n- ManyToOne relationships with Account (LAZY) and Quote (EAGER)\n- Validation: @Positive for quantity and purchasePrice\n\n---\n\n## 4. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/OrderDataBean.java\n\nOrder entity with 332 lines and named queries:\n- IDENTITY primary key generation\n- Fields: orderType, orderStatus, openDate, completionDate, quantity, price, orderFee\n- Named queries for finding and updating orders\n- ManyToOne relationships with Account and Quote\n- OneToOne with Holding\n- Business methods: isBuy(), isSell(), isOpen(), isCompleted(), cancel()\n\n---\n\n## 5. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/QuoteDataBean.java\n\nQuote entity representing stock quotes with 227 lines:\n- Symbol as primary key\n- Fields: companyName, volume, price, open1, low, high, change1\n- Named query: allQuotes\n- Named native query: quoteForUpdate (uses FOR UPDATE lock)\n\n---\n\n## 6. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java\n\nMarket summary bean with 186 lines:\n- TSIA (Trade Stock Index Average) tracking\n- Collections of top gainers and losers\n- Volume tracking\n- HTML formatting methods\n- Migration note indicates removal of javax.json dependency\n\n---\n\n## 7. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/beans/RunStatsDataBean.java\n\nStatistics bean with 295 lines tracking:\n- Trade user and stock counts\n- Login/logout counts\n- Order statistics (buy, sell, cancelled, open, deleted orders)\n- Holding counts\n\n---\n\n## 8. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessageProducerService.java\n\nMessage producer service with 149 lines - key migration artifact:\n- **MIGRATION**: JMS to SmallRye Reactive Messaging\n- Uses @Channel and Emitter pattern instead of JMS ConnectionFactory\n- Two channels: trade-broker-queue and trade-streamer-topic\n- Methods: queueOrderForProcessing(), sendBrokerPing(), publishQuoteUpdate(), publishQuotePriceChange(), sendStreamerPing()\n\n---\n\n## 9. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/OrderMessage.java\n\nOrder message POJO with 129 lines:\n- **MIGRATION**: Replaces JMS TextMessage properties\n- Fields: command, orderID, twoPhase, direct, publishTime, text\n- Factory methods: newOrder(), ping()\n- Commands: \"neworder\", \"ping\"\n\n---\n\n## 10. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/QuoteUpdateMessage.java\n\nQuote update message POJO with 195 lines:\n- **MIGRATION**: Replaces JMS Topic messages\n- Fields: command, symbol, price, oldPrice, publishTime, company, open, low, high, volume, changeFactor, sharesTraded\n- Factory methods: quoteUpdate(), ping()\n- Commands: \"updateQuote\", \"ping\"\n\n---\n\n## 11. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTBroker3MDB.java\n\nOrder processing MDB with 159 lines:\n- **MIGRATION**: @MessageDriven → @ApplicationScoped + @Incoming(\"trade-broker-queue\")\n- @Transactional replaces EJB transaction attributes\n- Processes \"neworder\" and \"ping\" commands\n- Exception handling triggers rollback\n- Uses MDBStats for performance tracking\n\n---\n\n## 12. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/mdb/DTStreamer3MDB.java\n\nQuote streaming MDB with 137 lines:\n- **MIGRATION**: @MessageDriven → @ApplicationScoped + @Incoming(\"trade-streamer-topic\")\n- Processes \"updateQuote\" and \"ping\" commands\n- Logs quote price changes\n- Performance tracking via MDBStats\n\n---\n\n## 13. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeConfig.java\n\nConfiguration utility with 425 lines:\n- Runtime mode configuration (DIRECT_JPA, DIRECT_JDBC, EJB3, SESSION_TO_DIRECT)\n- Order processing modes (SYNCH, ASYNCH, ASYNCH_2PHASE)\n- Database scaling parameters (MAX_USERS, MAX_QUOTES, MAX_HOLDINGS)\n- Random data generation methods\n- Scenario mixing for load testing\n- Penny stock and stock split configuration\n\n---\n\n## 14. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java\n\nAnnotationLiteral implementation with 36 lines:\n- Extends AnnotationLiteral<RuntimeMode>\n- Used for CDI qualifier instantiation\n\n---\n\n## 15. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/FinancialUtils.java\n\nFinancial calculation utilities with 113 lines:\n- **MIGRATION**: Updated to use RoundingMode enum instead of deprecated BigDecimal constants\n- Methods: computeGain(), computeGainPercent(), computeHoldingsTotal()\n- HTML formatting for gains/losses with arrows\n\n---\n\n## 16. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/KeyBlock.java\n\nKey block iterator with 140 lines:\n- Extends AbstractSequentialList\n- Provides sequential integer key generation\n- Used for primary key block allocation\n\n---\n\n## 17. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/Log.java\n\nLogging utility with 177 lines:\n- Uses java.util.logging.Logger\n- Methods: log(), error(), trace(), debug(), stat()\n- Collection printing utilities\n- Note: Could migrate to JBoss Logging in Quarkus\n\n---\n\n## 18. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/MDBStats.java\n\nMDB statistics tracker with 69 lines:\n- Singleton pattern\n- Extends HashMap<String, TimerStat>\n- Tracks message processing timing statistics\n- Methods: addTiming(), reset()\n\n---\n\n## 19. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java\n\nRecent quote changes tracker with 73 lines:\n- @ApplicationScoped bean\n- Maintains last 5 stock price changes\n- Fires CDI events via @QuotePriceChange qualifier\n- Thread-safe using CopyOnWriteArrayList\n- Used by WebSocket and SSE endpoints\n\n---\n\n## 20. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TimerStat.java\n\nTiming statistics bean with 134 lines:\n- Tracks min, max, totalTime, count\n- Methods return values in seconds\n- Used by MDBStats for performance metrics\n\n---\n\n## 21. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/TradeResourceTest.java\n\nBasic Quarkus test with 20 lines:\n- @QuarkusTest annotation\n- Tests market summary endpoint (/rest/trade/market)\n- Uses RestAssured\n\n---\n\n## 22. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingResourceTest.java\n\nMessaging endpoint tests with 120 lines:\n- Tests ping to broker and streamer\n- Tests statistics endpoints\n- Tests default message handling\n- Verifies async message processing\n\n---\n\n## 23. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingTest.java\n\nIntegration tests for messaging migration with 110 lines:\n- Tests MessageProducerService directly\n- Verifies MDB message processing via MDBStats\n- Tests: broker ping, streamer ping, quote updates\n- Includes async order processing test via REST API\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nAll 23 files have been read completely. The codebase represents a **Jakarta EE to Quarkus migration** of the IBM DayTrader sample application, with particular focus on:\n\n1. **JPA entities** (5 files) - migrated from javax.* to jakarta.* \n2. **Data beans** (2 files) - business logic and statistics\n3. **Messaging layer** (5 files) - **critical migration** from JMS to SmallRye Reactive Messaging\n4. **Utility classes** (8 files) - configuration, logging, statistics, financial calculations\n5. **Tests** (3 files) - Quarkus test framework with RestAssured\n\nThe most significant migration work is in the **messaging layer** where JMS Queue/Topic patterns were replaced with Reactive Messaging @Channel/@Emitter/@Incoming patterns."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"9806a101-861d-4677-aeb8-3f4f06bb0258"}
