{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QdWsBgJJUCF2bAYSpg8mMG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully created a new Spring Boot 3.x pom.xml file for migrating from Quarkus. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nThe new **pom.xml** file at `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/pom.xml` has been created with the following changes:\n\n### Project Coordinates\n- **groupId**: Changed to `com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader`\n- **artifactId**: Changed to `daytrader-spring` (from daytrader-quarkus)\n- **version**: Maintained at `1.0-SNAPSHOT`\n- **Parent**: Now uses `spring-boot-starter-parent` version 3.2.5\n\n### Java Version\n- Java 17 configured via `java.version`, `maven.compiler.source`, and `maven.compiler.target` properties\n\n### Dependency Mapping (Quarkus to Spring Boot)\nThe following Quarkus dependencies were replaced with Spring Boot 3.x equivalents:\n\n1. **REST API**: `quarkus-rest` → `spring-boot-starter-web`\n2. **JPA/Hibernate**: `quarkus-hibernate-orm` → `spring-boot-starter-data-jpa`\n3. **Validation**: `quarkus-hibernate-validator` → `spring-boot-starter-validation`\n4. **Health Checks**: `quarkus-smallrye-health` → `spring-boot-starter-actuator`\n5. **WebSocket**: `quarkus-websockets` → `spring-boot-starter-websocket`\n6. **H2 Database**: `quarkus-jdbc-h2` → `h2` (runtime scope)\n7. **JSON Processing**: `quarkus-rest-jackson` → `jackson-databind`\n8. **Testing**: `quarkus-junit5` → `spring-boot-starter-test`\n\n### Build Configuration\n- **spring-boot-maven-plugin**: Configured for packaging as executable JAR\n- **maven-compiler-plugin**: Set to compile with Java 17\n\nThe pom.xml is now ready for a Spring Boot 3.2.5 application and includes all the essential dependencies needed to migrate the DayTrader application from Quarkus."}]}]},"parent_tool_us