{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014kCWRTKirC1hv2wWy4fqxU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017QPWWtUCRRXG9QWhzSvfqT","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Write config and main class","prompt":"Write the following files for a Quarkus to Spring Boot migration. Use the Write tool for each file.\n\nFILE 1: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/resources/application.properties\n\nContent:\n```\n# Spring Boot Application Configuration\n# Migrated from Quarkus application.properties\n\nspring.application.name=daytrader\nserver.port=8080\n\n# Database Configuration\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\nspring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.h2.Driver\n\n# JPA/Hibernate\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n\n# Trade Application Configuration\ntrade.runtime-mode=EJB3\ntrade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\ntrade.max-users=50\ntrade.max-quotes=100\ntrade.db.populate.on.startup=true\n\n# Actuator\nmanagement.endpoints.web.exposure.include=health,info\nmanagement.endpoint.health.show-details=always\n\n# Jackson\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n\n# Logging\nlogging.level.com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader=INFO\n```\n\nFILE 2: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\nContent (this is the Spring Boot main class):\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@EnableAsync\npublic class DayTraderApplication {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFILE 3: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/Dockerfile\n\nContent:\n```\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\n# install uv\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\n# create venv and install\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy all the assets\nCOPY . .\n\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n\n# Build the application at image build time\nRUN mvn clean install -DskipTests\n\nCMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n```\n\nRead each file first, then write. Make sure all files are written correctly.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1322,"cache_read_input_tokens":123854,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1322,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3657},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"63e86e1c-de65-4789-a1b8-73f7e861b80a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014kCWRTKirC1hv2wWy4fqxU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWNzNB3zYkkBDdWDwyex9s","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate REST controllers","prompt":"Migrate the following JAX-RS REST controllers from Quarkus to Spring MVC. Write each file using the Write tool after reading it first.\n\nIMPORTANT: The original Quarkus app used `quarkus.rest.path=/rest` so all JAX-RS paths were prefixed with `/rest`. In Spring Boot, we need to explicitly add `/rest` prefix to the controller paths.\n\nFILE 1: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java\n\nMigrate from JAX-RS to Spring MVC:\n- @Path(\"trade\") → @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/trade\")\n- @GET → @GetMapping\n- @POST → @PostMapping  \n- @PathParam → @PathVariable\n- @FormParam → @RequestParam\n- @Produces(APPLICATION_JSON) → produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE\n- @Consumes(APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED) → consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED_VALUE\n- @Inject → @Autowired\n- @RequestScoped → (not needed)\n- Response.ok(entity).build() → ResponseEntity.ok(entity)\n- Response.serverError() → ResponseEntity.status(500)\n- Response.status(UNAUTHORIZED) → ResponseEntity.status(401)\n- Response.status(NOT_FOUND) → ResponseEntity.notFound()\n\nThe class should inject TradeServices (which is now a Spring bean). Replace `@Inject TradeServices tradeService;` with `@Autowired private TradeServices tradeService;`\n\nWrite the complete migrated file.\n\nFILE 2: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java\n\nSame migration pattern. @Path(\"quotes\") → @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\nKeep the same business logic.\n\nFILE 3: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/MessagingResource.java\n\nSame migration pattern. @Path(\"/messaging\") → @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/messaging\")\n@Inject MessageProducerService → @Autowired\n\nFILE 4: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/TradeAppResource.java\n\nThis is the web UI controller. Migrate it to:\n- @Controller + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/app\")\n- Use @ResponseBody on methods or return ResponseEntity<String>\n- Keep same HTML building logic\n- Change footer text from \"Quarkus Edition\" to \"Spring Boot Edition\"\n\nRead each file first, then write each using the Write tool. Make sure all files are written correctly.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1322,"cache_read_input_tokens":123854,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1322,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3657},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"fecefc0b-8045-4b8a-8a24-b21a4d5576d8"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014kCWRTKirC1hv2wWy4fqxU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017hN2QqxvXaAZYMu4PSsKBT","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate interfaces and qualifiers","prompt":"Migrate the CDI qualifier annotations and interfaces to Spring annotations. The CDI @Qualifier pattern needs to be replaced with Spring's @Qualifier pattern. Since Spring doesn't have the same CDI qualifier system, we'll use a simpler approach with Spring @Qualifier strings.\n\nRead each file first then write each using the Write tool.\n\nFILE 1: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeServices.java\n\nKeep this interface unchanged - it uses no CDI/Quarkus annotations. It only uses java and entity imports.\n\nFILE 2: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeJDBC.java\n\nReplace CDI @Qualifier with Spring @Qualifier. Since Spring doesn't support custom qualifier annotations the same way, convert this to a simple Spring qualifier annotation:\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.*;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n\n@Qualifier\n@Retention(RUNTIME)\n@Target({TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER})\npublic @interface TradeJDBC {}\n```\n\nFILE 3: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeEJB.java\n\nSame pattern - replace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier\n\nFILE 4: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeSession2Direct.java\n\nSame pattern.\n\nFILE 5: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/RuntimeMode.java\n\nReplace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier.\n\nFILE 6: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/Trace.java\n\nRemove the Jakarta interceptor binding. Convert to a simple annotation (not used functionally in Spring):\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Inherited;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n\n@Inherited\n@Target({ TYPE, METHOD })\n@Retention(RUNTIME)\npublic @interface Trace {}\n```\n\nFILE 7: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/MarketSummaryUpdate.java\n\nReplace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier.\n\nFILE 8: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/QuotePriceChange.java\n\nReplace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier.\n\nFILE 9: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeDB.java\n\nKeep unchanged - no CDI annotations.\n\nFILE 10: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java\n\nThis class extends jakarta.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral which doesn't exist in Spring. Simplify it to just implement RuntimeMode:\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Annotation;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n\npublic class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral implements RuntimeMode {\n    private static final long serialVersionUID = -252789556335033400L;\n    private String value;\n    \n    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String value() {\n        return value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Class<? extends Annotation> annotationType() {\n        return RuntimeMode.class;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nRead each file first, then write each file.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1322,"cache_read_input_tokens":123854,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1322,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3657},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"7cb9ee74-b112-4f49-9a23-4fc751d32f42"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write the following files for a Quarkus to Spring Boot migration. Use the Write tool for each file.\n\nFILE 1: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/resources/application.properties\n\nContent:\n```\n# Spring Boot Application Configuration\n# Migrated from Quarkus application.properties\n\nspring.application.name=daytrader\nserver.port=8080\n\n# Database Configuration\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\nspring.datasource.driver-class-name=org.h2.Driver\n\n# JPA/Hibernate\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n\n# Trade Application Configuration\ntrade.runtime-mode=EJB3\ntrade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\ntrade.max-users=50\ntrade.max-quotes=100\ntrade.db.populate.on.startup=true\n\n# Actuator\nmanagement.endpoints.web.exposure.include=health,info\nmanagement.endpoint.health.show-details=always\n\n# Jackson\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n\n# Logging\nlogging.level.com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader=INFO\n```\n\nFILE 2: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\nContent (this is the Spring Boot main class):\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;\n\n@SpringBootApplication\n@EnableScheduling\n@EnableAsync\npublic class DayTraderApplication {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFILE 3: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/Dockerfile\n\nContent:\n```\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\n# install uv\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\n# create venv and install\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy all the assets\nCOPY . .\n\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n\n# Build the application at image build time\nRUN mvn clean install -DskipTests\n\nCMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n```\n\nRead each file first, then write. Make sure all files are written correctly."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017QPWWtUCRRXG9QWhzSvfqT","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"1fb7b053-0c6b-4be8-be18-2f6385ac4d97"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migrate the following JAX-RS REST controllers from Quarkus to Spring MVC. Write each file using the Write tool after reading it first.\n\nIMPORTANT: The original Quarkus app used `quarkus.rest.path=/rest` so all JAX-RS paths were prefixed with `/rest`. In Spring Boot, we need to explicitly add `/rest` prefix to the controller paths.\n\nFILE 1: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/TradeResource.java\n\nMigrate from JAX-RS to Spring MVC:\n- @Path(\"trade\") → @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/trade\")\n- @GET → @GetMapping\n- @POST → @PostMapping  \n- @PathParam → @PathVariable\n- @FormParam → @RequestParam\n- @Produces(APPLICATION_JSON) → produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE\n- @Consumes(APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED) → consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED_VALUE\n- @Inject → @Autowired\n- @RequestScoped → (not needed)\n- Response.ok(entity).build() → ResponseEntity.ok(entity)\n- Response.serverError() → ResponseEntity.status(500)\n- Response.status(UNAUTHORIZED) → ResponseEntity.status(401)\n- Response.status(NOT_FOUND) → ResponseEntity.notFound()\n\nThe class should inject TradeServices (which is now a Spring bean). Replace `@Inject TradeServices tradeService;` with `@Autowired private TradeServices tradeService;`\n\nWrite the complete migrated file.\n\nFILE 2: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/QuoteResource.java\n\nSame migration pattern. @Path(\"quotes\") → @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\nKeep the same business logic.\n\nFILE 3: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/jaxrs/MessagingResource.java\n\nSame migration pattern. @Path(\"/messaging\") → @RestController + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/messaging\")\n@Inject MessageProducerService → @Autowired\n\nFILE 4: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/web/TradeAppResource.java\n\nThis is the web UI controller. Migrate it to:\n- @Controller + @RequestMapping(\"/rest/app\")\n- Use @ResponseBody on methods or return ResponseEntity<String>\n- Keep same HTML building logic\n- Change footer text from \"Quarkus Edition\" to \"Spring Boot Edition\"\n\nRead each file first, then write each using the Write tool. Make sure all files are written correctly."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BWNzNB3zYkkBDdWDwyex9s","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"4490a329-739e-4ced-b930-39439914d269"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Migrate the CDI qualifier annotations and interfaces to Spring annotations. The CDI @Qualifier pattern needs to be replaced with Spring's @Qualifier pattern. Since Spring doesn't have the same CDI qualifier system, we'll use a simpler approach with Spring @Qualifier strings.\n\nRead each file first then write each using the Write tool.\n\nFILE 1: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeServices.java\n\nKeep this interface unchanged - it uses no CDI/Quarkus annotations. It only uses java and entity imports.\n\nFILE 2: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeJDBC.java\n\nReplace CDI @Qualifier with Spring @Qualifier. Since Spring doesn't support custom qualifier annotations the same way, convert this to a simple Spring qualifier annotation:\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.*;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n\n@Qualifier\n@Retention(RUNTIME)\n@Target({TYPE, METHOD, FIELD, PARAMETER})\npublic @interface TradeJDBC {}\n```\n\nFILE 3: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeEJB.java\n\nSame pattern - replace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier\n\nFILE 4: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeSession2Direct.java\n\nSame pattern.\n\nFILE 5: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/RuntimeMode.java\n\nReplace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier.\n\nFILE 6: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/Trace.java\n\nRemove the Jakarta interceptor binding. Convert to a simple annotation (not used functionally in Spring):\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Inherited;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.METHOD;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.TYPE;\nimport static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME;\n\n@Inherited\n@Target({ TYPE, METHOD })\n@Retention(RUNTIME)\npublic @interface Trace {}\n```\n\nFILE 7: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/MarketSummaryUpdate.java\n\nReplace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier.\n\nFILE 8: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/QuotePriceChange.java\n\nReplace jakarta.inject.Qualifier with org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier.\n\nFILE 9: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/interfaces/TradeDB.java\n\nKeep unchanged - no CDI annotations.\n\nFILE 10: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java\n\nThis class extends jakarta.enterprise.util.AnnotationLiteral which doesn't exist in Spring. Simplify it to just implement RuntimeMode:\n\n```java\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.Annotation;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n\npublic class TradeRunTimeModeLiteral implements RuntimeMode {\n    private static final long serialVersionUID = -252789556335033400L;\n    private String value;\n    \n    public TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(String value) {\n        this.value = value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String value() {\n        return value;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Class<? extends Annotation> annotationType() {\n        return RuntimeMode.class;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nRead each file first, then write each file."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017hN2QqxvXaAZYMu4PSsKBT","session_id":"b6271ebd-2120-4e7f-8b1b-494582b368b5","uuid":"399a5b3c-cccd-4f11-a875-a67a18683a27"}
